The issue occurs because according to the [docs][1] the `getStyleProperty` method returns the computed value of width, which means that the value is returned in pixels, while you want to check the value in percents.

As a solution, I recommend you use the [ClientFunctions][2] mechanism, which allows you to get the desired value.

I prepared a sample for you:

    &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
    &lt;html lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
    &lt;head&gt;
        &lt;meta charset=&quot;UTF-8&quot;&gt;
        &lt;title&gt;Title&lt;/title&gt;
        &lt;style&gt;
            .bar {
                width: 500px;
                height: 50px;
                border: 1px solid black;
                overflow: hidden;
            }
    
            .progress {
                height: 100%;
                background-color: black;
            }
        &lt;/style&gt;
    &lt;/head&gt;
    &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;bar&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;progress&quot; style=&quot;width: 0;&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;script&gt;
        setInterval(function () {
            var progress = document.querySelector(&#39;.progress&#39;);
    
            progress.style.width = Math.min(100, parseInt(progress.style.width) + 1) + &#39;%&#39;;
        }, 50);
    &lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;/body&gt;
    &lt;/html&gt;

And here is the test code:

    import { Selector, ClientFunction } from &#39;testcafe&#39;;
    
    fixture `progress`
        .page `index.html`;
    
    const getStyleWidthInPercents = ClientFunction(() =&gt; {
        return document.querySelector(&#39;.progress&#39;).style.width;
    });
    
    test(&#39;progress&#39;, async t =&gt; {
        await t.expect(getStyleWidthInPercents()).eql(&#39;100%&#39;, {timeout: 90000})
    });


  [1]: https://devexpress.github.io/testcafe/documentation/test-api/selecting-page-elements/dom-node-state.html#members-specific-to-element-nodes
  [2]: https://devexpress.github.io/testcafe/documentation/test-api/obtaining-data-from-the-client/

