Like Magnus said, variables in PHP have different scopes [Variable scope][1], You can&#39;t reach it out of the scope. In your code, `$v3` can only be reached inside the function `applican()`, but not `index.php`. You can extend the variable&#39;s scope with keyword `global`:

    &lt;?php # inc/send.php
        function applican(){
            global $v3;
            $v3 = $_POST[&#39;v3&#39;];
        };

Or other solution like:

    &lt;?php # inc/send.php
        function applican(){
            return $_POST[&#39;v3&#39;];
        };

    &lt;?php # index.php
        $v3 = applican(); echo $v3;

  [1]: https://www.php.net/manual/en/language.variables.scope.php

