The role of the test driver is to execute tests you have previously defined and give you results for each of them. You can write your own custom test driver/framework, however, I would encourage you to use an existing one such as Google test, or any listed in this [other thread][1].

The tests are written to give you confidence over the logic defined in these `min`/`max` functions, and would verify some expectations. For example, with Google Test, you could write something like this:

    TEST(MyMathModule, minWorks) {
        EXPECT_EQ(myMin(1, 5), 1);
    }

Here is an additional [link][2] about the purpose of unit testing if you need more information.


  [1]: https://stackoverflow.com/a/65845/6765574
